autenja/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kautenja/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kautenja/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kautenja/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kautenja/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2018-06-14T16:11:09Z", "updated_at": "2018-06-15T00:45:31Z", "closed_at": "2018-06-15T00:45:31Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I'm seeing a spurious issue where after tagging a new release, `setuptools-git-version` continues to use the last tag. I can tag several releases, and running setup.py continuously fails to use the up to date tag. Is there some caching mechanism in place that is misbehaving? Unfortunately, I cannot reproduce the error reliably, though it has happened at least 5 times in the span of one week", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pyfidelity/setuptools-git-version/issues/7", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pyfidelity/setuptools-git-version", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pyfidelity/setuptools-git-version/issues/7/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pyfidelity/setuptools-git-version/issues/7/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pyfidelity/setuptools-git-version/issues/7/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pyfidelity/setuptools-git-version/issues/7", "id": 201953432, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyMDE5NTM0MzI=", "number": 7, "title": "Question: omitting the git hash for builds from tagged commits", "user": {"login": "brianwallace", "id": 1696507, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2OTY1MDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/1696507?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/brianwallace", "ht